gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Trail Blazers 119, Bucks 116
gameRecap.excerpt: The Trail Blazers held on late to defeat the Bucks, 119-116, in Damian Lillards return to Portland. Anfernee Simons (24 points, three rebounds, five assists) and Deandre Ayton (20 points, 11 rebounds) led the Blazers as they improved to 15-33. Giannis Antetokounmpo (27 points, eight rebounds, four assists, three steals) led Milwaukee as Damian Lillard (25 points, six rebounds, seven assists) and Khris Middleton (21 points, eight assists) totaled 46 points for Milwaukee. The Bucks move to 32-16.
